/*
 * File : lexer.hpp
 * statically typed, doesnt follow strict python syntax
 *
 * Will start initially with 3 data types CHAR, INT, FLOAT, STRING, might add ARRAY<INT | STRING | FLOAT | CHAR> and 
 * STRUCT later
 *
 * functions will be defined with FUNCTION keyword and return type must be specified after colon
 *
 * STRINGS will be dynamically sized, no need to handle allocation and deallocation by user
 * INT STRING_SIZE(STRING param); and the indexing operator will be provided by default, strings will be immutable
 * 
 * FUNCTIONS can have VOID return type
 *
 * example function:
 * 
 * FUNCTION foo(INT param1, STRING param2) : INT {
 *	FLOAT k = param1 - 5.64;
 *	RETURN k; 
 * } 
 *
 *
 * Scopes and all blocks will be defined use c-style curly braces {}, braces define scope
 * White space does not matter as long as scope is respected
 *
 * comments will be single line python style comments anything follow by `'#' till \n [#.*]
 * 
 * STRUCTS maybe added but language will not support classes or object oriented style of programming
 *
 * Will not have for loops, but will support while loops, syntax:
 * While loops support BREAK; and CONTINUE; 
 * 
 * WHILE(condition){
 *	body
 * }
 *
 * If statements will also follow the same predictable syntax
 *
 * IF(condition){
 *	body
 * }
 *
 * ELIF(condition){ #optional
 *	body
 * }
 *
 * ELSE{  #optional
 *	body
 * }
 *
 * will support all basic operations + - * / % && || & | ^ ! < > <= >= == != []
 *
 * INT op INT -> INT
 * FLOAT op INT -> FLOAT
 * FLOAT op FLOAT -> FLOAT
 * STRING op INT | FLOAT -> compiler error
 * CHAR -> INT and INT -> CHAR is legal (cast char to its ascii value)
 *
 * INT is garunteed 64 bits and FLOAT is garunteed 64 bits and CHAR is garunteed 1 byte
 *
 * Statement not ending in a semi colon will cause exception
 * Not closing a string or a block will cause an error
 * Accessing out of scope variable or function will cause error
 * Attempting use a void function in assignment will cause error
 * Illegal type cast will cause error
 * Probably will add a lot more error
 * Keywords for language are made all caps for ease of recognitio
 *
 * 
 * lexer will be constructed with regexes using: https://cse.msu.edu/~cse450/Emplex/Emplex.html
 *
 * find the regular expressions used to generate lexer in lexer.emplex file
 *
 * */

/// OPERATOR TOKEN \*\*|&&|\|\||<=|>=|==|!=|[+\-*/%&|^!<>\[\]]


